ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd highly recommend this course to fellow students interested in human neuroimaging techniques.

"The lab meeting is technically oriented and we work through all the different steps in fMRI analysis in the different imaging packages. It's really useful for understanding why each parameter helps or hurts the data analysis, and I recommend it for anyone doing fMRI analysis."

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course directly contributed to my research through the focus on both fMRI analysis issues and connectivity methods.
Understanding the details of fMRI analysis is essential for understanding the results of fMRI studies. This lab meeting also helped me understand the choices I make when analyzing my fMRI data.
